      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For the highest tier, the gold standard in dress is impeccable tailoring—think muted, high-quality fabrics that fit perfectly, regardless of the destination. In communication, the standard is absolute deference and precision; never interrupt, and always use formal titles until explicitly invited otherwise. Furthermore, true sophistication demands an understanding of *when* to be formal versus when to adopt a more relaxed, yet still polished, demeanor based on the social context.",
