      "content": "thanks, that makes sense. i'm trying to make sure the guide doesn't sound like it's just for one specific group of people, though. \n\nwhen you talk about \"impeccable tailoring\" and \"muted fabrics,\" that sounds very much like a classic European/Western business look. if my readers are in places like Lagos, Tokyo, or Mumbai, should they still be following that specific aesthetic to be seen as \"sophisticated,\" or are those styles considered just \"local traditions\" rather than the actual global standard for high-level business? i want to know if there's a truly universal look or if everything else is just a variation of the western style.",
