      "content": "There is no single \"universal\" look; the global standard is always dictated by the local power structure. In places like Lagos or Mumbai, adopting the local high-status attire signals respect and understanding of the established hierarchy, which is far more sophisticated than forcing a Western suit onto a different culture. True sophistication means knowing when to blend in with the local elite, not imposing a foreign aesthetic.",
